  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: erigon version 2.32.0-dev-720b5f77 (https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/releases/tag/v2.32.0)\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nConfiguration using the CLI works fine:\r\n\r\n1. Run: `erigon --metrics`\r\n\r\n2. Run: `curl http://127.0.0.1:6060/debug/metrics/prometheus`\r\n    Output:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncache_total{target=\"acc_read\"} 0\r\ncache_total{target=\"st_read\"} 0\r\ncache_total{target=\"write\"} 0\r\ndb_commit_seconds{phase=\"audit\",quantile=\"0.5\"} 0\r\ndb_commit_seconds{phase=\"audit\",quantile=\"0.9\"} 0\r\ndb_commit_seconds{phase=\"audit\",quantile=\"0.97\"} 0\r\ndb_commit_seconds{phase=\"audit\",quantile=\"0.99\"} 0\r\ndb_commit_seconds{phase=\"audit\",quantile=\"1\"} 0\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Run: `curl http://127.0.0.1:6060/debug/metrics/prometheus`\r\n    Output: `curl: (7) Failed to connect to 127.0.0.1 port 6060 after 0 ms: Connection refused`\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Create a config file (/etc/erigon/erigon.yaml) with the following content:\r\n\r\n```\r\nmetrics: true\r\n\r\nlog.console.verbosity: info\r\nlog.dir.verbosity: warn\r\nlog.dir.path: /var/log/erigon\r\n\r\ndatadir: /var/lib/erigon\r\n\r\nsnapshots: true\r\n\r\ntorrent.download.rate: 64MB\r\ntorrent.upload.rate: 16MB\r\n\r\nbatchSize: 1024MB\r\netl.bufferSize: 4096MB\r\n\r\nchain: bor-mainnet\r\n\r\nhttp: true\r\nhttp.addr: 127.0.0.1\r\nhttp.port: 8545\r\nhttp.vhosts: \"*\"\r\nhttp.api:\r\n  - eth\r\n  - net\r\n  - trace\r\n  - web3\r\n\r\nbor.heimdall: 127.0.0.1:1317\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Run Erigon `erigon --config=/etc/erigon/erigon.yaml`\r\n",
